const technomancy = "## [Front-End Developer | modern web apps](https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/~01527a09cdcfd75500?s=1110580755057594368)\n\n### I work with Vue.js, React, LAMP stacks, Node.js, and cloud platforms like AWS and Google Cloud. \n\nExperienced in Python (Flask, Django), PHP, SQL/NoSQL, and Linux environments — which \nmeans I can comfortably connect front-end and back-end systems.  \n\n**I help teams and businesses turn ideas into polished apps using:**\n\n- Component-based architectures\n- API integrations\n- Responsive UI frameworks (Tailwind, Bootstrap, Material UI)\n- Performance optimization and best practices\n\n**If you need someone who can jump into your Vue or React project, clean things up, or help you ship confidently, let’s talk!**\n\n### 🛠️ Core Skills  \n\n   \n- HTML | CSS | JavaScript  \n- Vue.js | React.js | Nuxt.js | Next.js  \n- Tailwind | Bootstrap | Sass  \n- Node.js | REST API Integration  \n- Firebase | Supabase  \n- Python Flask | Django | FastAPI  \n- Git / GitHub  \n- Linux / LAMP Stack  \n\nMy projects include SaaS dashboards, marketing sites, admin panels, and small business web apps. I love transforming complex ideas into fast, responsive, user-friendly interfaces. With experience across both startup MVPs and production apps, I focus on delivering clean, maintainable code, beautiful interfaces, and great user experiences.\n\n* * *\n\n## [📊 Data Automation & Analytics 🐍](https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/~01527a09cdcfd75500)\n\n### Process automation, data flow connections and configuration, custom dashboard data insights and MVP prototypes. I help organizations move smoothly from raw data to actionable intelligence using the right blend of Python tools, scripting, APIs, and visualization platforms.\n\n| Core Skills | Tools |\n| ----------- | ----- |\n| Python (Pandas, NumPy, Automation, PDF processing) | Power BI, Excel, Google Sheets |\n| ETL workflows and data pipelines | Flask, FastAPI, REST APIs |\n| Automation, scripting, and data cleaning | SQL, MySQL, NoSQL |\n| Dashboard development and reporting | Firebase, Google Cloud, Compute Engine |\n| Software integration across cloud platforms | Linux, Docker, Git |\n\n\n**With a background bridging tech, economics, and the arts, I’ve evolved into a problem-solver who thrives on making messy data useful. I’ve worked across industries, handling:**\n\n- Automating PDF → CSV extraction for bulk certificate processing  \n- Building Python tools for scraping, parsing, and transforming data  \n- Designing Power BI dashboards for executive KPIs  \n- Connecting cloud platforms like Google Cloud + MS365 with Python scripts and APIs  \n- Supporting cross-team data validation, reporting, and compliance  \n\n* * *\n\n### ⚙️ What I Build:\n\n*   Custom dashboards with KPIs and visualizations\n*   Automated reports using Python, Google Sheets & Google APIs\n*   Backend tools to sync CRMs, ERPs, and spreadsheets\n*   Simple web UIs for data entry and review\n\n### 💼 Typical Clients:\n\n*   Small medical practices & operational teams\n*   Agencies & B2B service providers\n*   Coaches, consultants, and solo operators\n\n### 🛠️ My Stack:\n\n*   Python (Flask or FastAPI), SQL/NoSQL\n*   Google Workspace / Apps Script\n*   React / Vue / Firebase\n*   Bash scripting & Linux server automation\n\n### 🎯 Skills at a Glance:\n\n*   Business intelligence reporting\n*   Database development & query writing\n*   Google Apps Script & spreadsheet automation\n*   Linux servers, cron jobs, CLI tools\n*   LAMP/PHP, Node.js, TypeScript\n*   CSS/SASS, UI frameworks & web design\n*   Graphic/media production and CMS work (WordPress, etc.)\n\n---\n\n## Background\n\nI started my career as a creative — performing, teaching, and producing music and video — before transitioning into software and analytics. Over several years, I’ve moved from self-taught coder to key team member, supporting high-growth startups and building a cloud-integrated ERP data system, used by hundreds of employees.\n\nMy eduction in economics grants a sharp analytical mindset, while my background in arts and yogas makes me adaptable, collaborative, and eager to learn.\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 My GitHub Portfolio\n\n- [pdf-coa-to-csv](https://github.com/invisispider/pdf-coa-to-csv) – Python tools that read PDF test certificates  \n- [web-scrape-realtors](https://github.com/invisispider/web-scrape-realtors) – Python web scraper for US realtors  \n- [mfa-metrc-login](https://github.com/invisispider/mfa-metrc-login) – Automates Metrc MFA login with backup codes  \n- [python-google-sheets-server](https://github.com/invisispider/python-google-sheets-server) – Flask server with Google API integration  \n- [Stein-Unlimited](https://github.com/invisispider/Stein-Unlimited) – Personal Vue 3 web app with advanced features  \n- [invisispider.github.io](https://github.com/invisispider/invisispider.github.io) – My portfolio site on GitHub Pages\n\n\n---\n\n## Let’s Connect\n\nIf you need a flexible, curious, and well-rounded developer with strong Python/data skills, I’m open to remote work, contract roles, or collaborations.\n\n#### 💼 [Upwork](https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/~01527a09cdcfd75500) \n\n#### 💬 [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/adam-loewen-3218ab48/)  \n";
